# .worktreeinclude
#
# Lists gitignored files/paths that `claude --worktree <name>` copies into
# each new worktree. A git worktree only checks out TRACKED files, so any
# file the app needs at runtime that is NOT tracked must be listed here
# (gitignore-style patterns, one per line).
#
# Checked 2026-05-21 for ADIAT — nothing is required here:
#   - AI Person Detector ONNX models
#     (app/algorithms/images/AIPersonDetector/services/*.onnx) are tracked.
#   - Native SDK binaries under app/external/ (exiftool.exe, DJI Thermal
#     SDK, Autel SDK .dll/.so/.lib) are tracked.
#   - No .env or local config files exist in the repo.
# A fresh worktree therefore already has everything needed to run the app;
# only the Python venv must be created per worktree (it cannot be copied).
#
# If a gitignored runtime file is added later, list it below, e.g.:
#   config.local.json
#   app/secrets/api_keys.json
